
[Richmond, 5 June 1780. JHD, May 1780, 1827 edn., p. 35 (5 June): The Speaker laid before the House a letter from the Governor, enclosing one from Governor Nash of North-Carolina, containing intelligence from Charleston. Not located, but see the letter from Nash, 30 May, which was enclosed, and TJ to Huntington, 9 June, which states that the first certain information of the surrender of Charleston on 12 May reached Richmond twenty-four days later, i.e., 5 June.]
